snippet: New Hampshire has one of the healthiest economies in the country, but voters are still deeply nervous about the nation’s fiscal health.
abstract: New Hampshire has one of the healthiest economies in the United States, but voters there are still deeply nervous about the nation's fiscal health; the high anxiety portends just how dominant the economy will be in the presidential campaign.

byline.contributor: Jess Bidgood contributed reporting from Concord, N.H.

lead_paragraph: New Hampshire has one of the healthiest economies in the country, but voters are still deeply nervous about the nation’s fiscal health.

headline.main: In New Hampshire, Fiscal Anxiety Despite Relative Economic Health
headline.print_headline: In New Hampshire, Fiscal Anxiety Despite Relative Economic Health
